      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Utility function (characterData.ts) imports from client-side Svelte stores, violating framework-agnostic abstraction boundary",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
        "related_files": [
          "src/lib/utils/characterData.ts",
          "src/stores.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "import { dungeonData, apiPopup, wowSummaryStore } from '../../stores'",
          "Stores imported are created with writable() from svelte/store, making them SvelteKit-specific",
          "characterData.ts exports fetchRuns() and fetchWowSummary() which mutate these stores directly inside utility functions",
          "This couples utility layer to component framework, preventing reuse in non-Svelte contexts"
