      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "browse-logs casts request.json() directly to its typed shape while sibling routes validate before trusting the body",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "mid_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "src/routes/api/browse-logs/+server.ts",
          "src/routes/api/fights/+server.ts",
          "src/lib/server/wclGraphQL.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "src/routes/api/browse-logs/+server.ts: `const params: BrowseLogsParams = await request.json();` \u2014 no shape check, no try around the parse, the cast pretends the boundary is typed",
          "src/routes/api/fights/+server.ts: `const body = (await request.json().catch(() => null)) as { code?: unknown } | null; ... if (typeof code !== 'string' || !code) return apiError('Invalid or missing report code.', 400);`",
          "src/lib/server/wclGraphQL.ts exports parseFightRequestBody() and handleWclFightRequest() and 5 per-fight endpoints flow through them; browse-logs is the obvious sibling that opted out",
          "A malformed POST to /api/browse-logs will throw an uncaught SyntaxError or coerce undefined fields into the SQL builder, where a sibling handler would have returned a clean 400"
        ],
        "suggestion": "Mirror the fights/+server.ts pattern in browse-logs: read the body as `unknown`, narrow each field (`typeof params.bossId === 'number'`, etc.) and return `apiError('Invalid browse-logs body', 400)` on failure. If this validation pattern keeps recurring, add a `parseBrowseLogsBody()` next to parseFightRequestBody in src/lib/server/wclGraphQL.ts (or a sibling validators module) so request-body parsing for /api routes lives in one place",
