    "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::db_index_barrel_blurs_two_database_boundary": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::db_index_barrel_blurs_two_database_boundary",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "src/lib/db/index.ts barrel re-exports user-DB modules, eroding the documented two-database boundary at the import surface",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
        "related_files": [
          "src/lib/db/index.ts",
          "src/lib/db/schema.ts",
          "src/lib/db/userSchema.ts",
          "src/lib/db/userDb.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "src/lib/db/index.ts ends with `export * from './userSchema'; export * from './users'; export * from './userRecents'; export { getUserDb } from './userDb'`, so `$lib/db` is both the raid-DB factory entry and a user-DB barrel.",
          "src/lib/db/schema.ts module doc explicitly defines two intentionally separate databases (DATABASE_URL raid analytics vs DATABASE_USER_URL user/auth) and points at userSchema.ts for the user side, contradicting the unified barrel.",
          "Real user-DB consumers do not use the barrel: api/character-reports, api/current-state, api/recent-reports, api/recent-characters all import directly from `$lib/db/userRecents.js`; data/myWowRoster.ts imports directly from `$lib/db/bnetAccount` and `$lib/db/userCharacters`; auth.ts imports `$lib/db/userDb.js`, `$lib/db/userSchema.js`, `$lib/db/users.js`. The user-DB half of the barrel has no active external need."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Make src/lib/db/index.ts the raid-DB entry only \u2014 export getRaidDb plus a curated re-export of schema.ts (raid tables) \u2014 and remove the user-DB re-exports. Either keep the existing direct imports for user-DB modules, or add a sibling barrel `src/lib/db/user/index.ts` that re-exports getUserDb + userSchema + users + userRecents and migrate the four user-DB consumers to it. Either way restores the documented two-database boundary at the import surface.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "966ff296"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-04-26T23:18:27+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-04-26T23:18:27+00:00",
