    "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::connection_factory_contract_drift": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::connection_factory_contract_drift",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Documented single-factory architecture in src/lib/db/connection.ts is not enforced \u2014 getRaidDb and getUserDb each inline the full client config",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
        "related_files": [
          "src/lib/db/connection.ts",
          "src/lib/db/index.ts",
          "src/lib/db/userDb.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "src/lib/db/connection.ts module doc states 'Both databases ... connect with identical client settings ... This module owns those settings so the two getXxxDb() wrappers ... differ only by the env var they read and the scope tag used for logging.' and exports createDrizzlePostgres for that purpose.",
          "src/lib/db/index.ts getRaidDb (lines ~7-50) and src/lib/db/userDb.ts getUserDb (lines ~7-52) each call postgres() directly with the same prepare/max/idle_timeout/connect_timeout/transform/types/onnotice/debug/fetch_types/max_lifetime block instead of calling createDrizzlePostgres.",
          "createDrizzlePostgres has zero importers in the workspace, making connection.ts a documented contract that runtime ignores \u2014 exactly the 'documented architecture contracts drifting from runtime' look-for of this dimension."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Either adopt the factory (rewrite getRaidDb in db/index.ts to `return createDrizzlePostgres({ label: 'raid', connectionString: env.DATABASE_URL, connectionStringSource: 'DATABASE_URL' })` and getUserDb similarly with DATABASE_USER_URL || DATABASE_URL), or delete connection.ts and update its module doc claim. Adopting is preferred \u2014 the factory already owns logServerError-based error reporting, which would also remove the lone `src/lib/db/ -> src/lib/server/` cross-directory edge once the dead file is removed from the import graph.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "061e151f"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-04-26T23:18:27+00:00",
