          "src/routes/api/character-score/+server.ts line 38-40: `if (!name || !region || !realm || !VALID_REGIONS.has(region)) { return apiOk({ score: null, color: null, source: null } satisfies ScoreResult, 400); }` \u2014 uses `apiOk` with a 400 status and the success-shape body.",
          "Every other endpoint in src/routes/api uses `apiError('...', 400)` for missing/invalid params (e.g. blizzard:14, calculate-runs:21-23, damage-average:14, death-hotspots:13, fights:43, browse-logs/various, spec-statistics:17, top-players:18-22), which produces `{error: string}` per src/lib/server/apiResponses.ts:7-9.",
          "A client doing `const data = await res.json(); if (data.error) ...` will silently treat the 400 as a successful null result instead of surfacing a parameter error."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Replace the 400 branch with `return apiError('Missing or invalid name/region/realm', 400);` to match the rest of the surface. Update the docblock that promises `400 ScoreResult` to instead document the standard `{error}` envelope.",
