    "review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::throws_never_misses_json_parse": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::throws_never_misses_json_parse",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 2,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "fetchRuns / fetchWowSummary document `@throws Never` but JSON parsing happens outside the try/catch, so SyntaxError can propagate.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "contract_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "src/lib/data/characterData.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "characterData.ts:42 JSDoc on fetchRuns: `@throws Never \u2014 network failures are surfaced as { kind: 'error', status: 0 }`. Implementation wraps only `response = await fetch(url)` in try/catch (lines 49-55); the subsequent `await response.json()` (line 60) and the `data.runs.slice(...)` mapping run with no error handler. A non-JSON body (HTML 503 page, truncated response) throws a SyntaxError that bypasses the documented FetchRunsResult contract.",
          "characterData.ts:92 fetchWowSummary repeats the same pattern: `@throws Never \u2014 non-OK responses are surfaced as { kind: 'error' }`, but `await response.json()` at line 110 is outside the fetch try/catch."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Either widen the try/catch in fetchRuns and fetchWowSummary to cover `response.json()` (returning `{ kind: 'error', status: response.status }` or `status: 0` on parse failure) or weaken the JSDoc to `@throws SyntaxError on malformed JSON; otherwise never throws`. The first option keeps callers' branching simple and matches the rest of the discriminated-union style used in the file.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "761864df"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-04-26T23:18:27+00:00",
