    "review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::bnet_refresh_silent_persist": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::bnet_refresh_silent_persist",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 2,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "refreshBattleNetToken's docstring promises persistence but the DB write's catch block silently swallows failures, so 'fresh token returned' does not imply 'tokens persisted'.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "contract_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "src/lib/db/bnetAccount.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "bnetAccount.ts:39-40 JSDoc: 'Refresh an expired Battle.net OAuth token using the stored refresh_token and persist the new values on the accounts row. Returns the fresh access token, or null when the refresh failed.' The contract pairs return value with persistence.",
          "bnetAccount.ts:88-99 implementation: the inner `try { db.update(accounts).set({...}) } catch { /* Ignore persistence failures here; callers can still use the fresh token. */ }` returns `payload.access_token` after a swallowed write. There is no log line, no telemetry, and no signal in the return type that persistence failed \u2014 the next call to getValidBattleNetUserToken will see stale stored tokens and trigger another refresh, which is the exact case the doc says won't happen."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Either (a) align the doc with the behavior \u2014 note that persistence is best-effort and a stale `expires_at` may persist \u2014 and route the failure through `logServerError('bnet/refresh', ...)` so a recurring failure is observable, or (b) honor the documented contract by letting the persistence error propagate (or returning null). Option (a) is the smaller change and matches the codebase's existing pattern for best-effort writes (auth.ts:96 logs and continues with a comment).",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "07749f9f"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-04-26T23:18:27+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-04-26T23:18:27+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "work_item_kind": "review_defect",
      "issue_kind": "review_defect",
      "origin": "review_import",
      "lang": "typescript",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::db_index_barrel_incomplete_and_unused": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::db_index_barrel_incomplete_and_unused",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 2,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "src/lib/db/index.ts re-exports a partial subset of the DB API (`userSchema`, `users`, `userRecents`) while omitting `bnetAccount` and `userCharacters`; no caller imports through it.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "contract_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "src/lib/db/index.ts",
          "src/lib/db/bnetAccount.ts",
          "src/lib/db/userCharacters.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "index.ts:55-58 contains `export * from './userSchema'; export * from './users'; export * from './userRecents'; export { getUserDb } from './userDb';` \u2014 bnetAccount.ts (getValidBattleNetUserToken, getBattleNetAccount) and userCharacters.ts (getStoredCharacters, replaceStoredCharacters, etc.) are equally public but missing.",
          "Grep across src/ shows every consumer imports concretely: auth.ts \u2192 '$lib/db/users.js' + '$lib/db/userSchema.js'; myWowRoster.ts \u2192 '$lib/db/bnetAccount' + '$lib/db/userCharacters'; routes/api/* \u2192 '$lib/db/userRecents.js'. Zero call sites use '$lib/db' or '$lib/db/index'. The barrel is effectively dead but its partiality misleads anyone who reads it as the public API contract for src/lib/db."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Pick one of: (a) delete the `export *` block entirely and keep getRaidDb only \u2014 concrete imports are already the project convention, or (b) make the barrel exhaustive by adding `export * from './userCharacters'` and `export * from './bnetAccount'`. Option (a) is simpler and matches the existing import pattern across auth.ts, myWowRoster.ts and the API routes.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "3b0fa83f"
      },
      "status": "open",
