      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "getUserRecents<T> casts unvalidated JSONB to RecentItem<T>[], so the generic promises a shape the runtime never checks",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "type_safety",
        "related_files": [
          "src/lib/db/userRecents.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Lines 138-163: getUserRecents<T = unknown>(...): Promise<RecentItem<T>[]> performs `getUserDb().select().from(userRecents)...` and returns `recents as unknown as RecentItem<T>[]`.",
          "The `entityData` column is JSONB and is written by addUserRecent with `entityData: unknown`; nothing in the read path narrows it to T, so callers passing e.g. `getUserRecents<CharacterRecentData>` receive items typed as CharacterRecentData but holding arbitrary parsed JSON."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Either drop the <T> generic and return `RecentItem<unknown>[]` so callers must narrow with the existing RecentEntityData discriminated union, or have getUserRecents accept the discriminator (`type: RecentEntityType`) and at runtime tag each row with the matching union variant before returning. Concretely: change the signature to `getUserRecents(userId: string, type?: RecentEntityType, limit?: number): Promise<RecentItem<unknown>[]>` and let callers `switch` on `r.type` against RecentEntityData.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "f4dfac5a"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
